<li>Superman #424-649 do not exist, however, the issues that took those numbers can be found on the <em><a href=\\\"\\/adventures-of-superman\\/4050-3778\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-3778\\\">Adventures of Superman<\\/a><\\/em> page.<\\/li><li>Another ongoing title from DC entitled <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/superman\\/4050-3816\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-3816\\\"><em>Superman<\\/em><\\/a> does exist and was published with its own numbering while <em>Adventures of Superman<\\/em> was in print, thus even though this title began publication in the 30's and lasted until 2011, no two Superman titles were hitting shelves at the same time.<\\/li><li>The main star of the series has of course been <a href=\\\"\\/superman\\/4005-1807\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-1807\\\">Superman<\\/a> but from #686-697 <a href=\\\"\\/mon-el\\/4005-21508\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-21508\\\">Mon-El<\\/a> was the star as Superman was away from Earth and the covers bore the banners \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/world-without-superman\\/4045-55848\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4045-55848\\\"><em>World Without Superman<\\/em><\\/a>\\\" for the first five and \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/world-against-superman\\/4045-55951\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4045-55951\\\"><em>World Against Superman<\\/em><\\/a>\\\" for the last six issues of this absence.<\\/li><li>For Post <a href=\\\"\\/flashpoint\\/4045-56280\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4045-56280\\\">Flashpoint<\\/a> volume 3, refer to <em><a href=\\\"\\/superman\\/4050-42986\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-42986\\\">Superman<\\/a><\\/em>.<\\/li><li>Click the link to view this title's annuals: <em><a href=\\\"\\/superman-annual\\/4050-2016\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-2016\\\">Superman Annual<\\/a>.<\\/em><\\/li><li>Click the liik to view this title's specials: <em><a href=\\\"\\/superman-special\\/4050-3205\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-3205\\\">Superman Special<\\/a><\\/em>.<\\/li><\\/ul><p> <\\/p>\",\"first_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.co