ues)<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/master-comics\\/4050-113374\\/\\\">Master Comics<\\/a> (#19)<\\/li><\\/ul><h4>Collected Editons:<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1228-the-complete-bulletman-vo\\/4000-681608\\/\\\">The Complete Bulletman Volume 6<\\/a> (#61-106)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1400-a-devils-dagger-treasury\\/4000-681708\\/\\\">A Devil's Dagger Treasury<\\/a> (selected DD stories from #1-20)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1935-the-golden-age-captain-ma\\/4000-682215\\/\\\">The Golden Age Captain Marvel: Volume 2<\\/a> (#21)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2075-the-golden-age-captain-ma\\/4000-680603\\/\\\">The Golden Age Captain Marvel: Volume 3<\\/a> (#20)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2051-golden-age-captain-marvel\\/4000-680761\\/\\\">Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr. Giant #1<\\/a> (#22-57)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2053-golden-age-captain-marvel\\/4000-685506\\/\\\">Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr. Giant #3<\\/a> (#60)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"first_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-110392\\/\",\"id\":110392,\"name\":\"The Origin of Master Man\",\"issue_number\":\"1\"},\"id\":839,\"image\":{\"icon_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_avatar\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"medium_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_medium\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"screen_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_medium\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"screen_large_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_kubrick\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"small_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_small\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"super_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_large\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"thumb_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_avatar\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"tiny_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_mini\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"original_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/original\\/134580-839-110392-1-master-comics.jpg\",\"image_tags\":\"All Images\"},\"last_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-389\\/\",\"id\":389,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"133\"},\"name\":\"Master Comics\",\"publisher\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/publisher\\/4010-34\\/\",\"id\":34,\"name\":\"Fawcett Publications\"},\"site_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/master-comics\\/4050-839\\/\",\"start_year\":\"1940\"},{\"aliases\":null,\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/volume\\/4050-843\\/\",\"count_of_issues\":155,\"date_added\":\"2008-06-06 11:08:04\",\"date_last_updated\":\"2018-10-01 14:41:40\",\"deck\":null,\"description\":\"<p>Whiz Comics #1 does not exist but rather it's non-existence is part of the troubled origins of the <a href=\\\"\\/billy-batson\\/4005-2350\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-2350\\\">Captain Marvel<\\/a> character. Fawcett was trying to secure rights to both the name of their character and title of his series but despite releasing two ashcan first issues (<a href=\\\"\\/flash-comics\\/4050-37851\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-37851\\\">Flash Comics<\\/a> #1 and <a href=\\\"\\/thrill-comics\\/4050-37850\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-37850\\\">Thrill Comics<\\/a> #1) in which their protagonist was named Captain Thunder...none of the rights were secured and so Captain Marvel and Whiz Comics were born. Although Captain Marvel was the feature character, like most comics of the period, it was an anthology featuring several different characters. The series had two third issues, which ended up balancing things out and making the fourth issue the actual fourth comic to bear the title Whiz Comics, a labeling it would keep up until the book's 155th and final issue.<\\/p><h4>Collected Editions:<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2090-captain-marvels-concentra\\/4000-680539\\/\\\">Captain Marvel's Concentrated Comics<\\/a> (#20, 51, 53, and 59)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1811-the-complete-adventures-o\\/4000-682100\\/\\\">The Complete Adventures of Captain Marvel and the Lieutenant Marvels<\\/a> (#21, 29, 34, 40)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1272-the-complete-singapore-sa\\/4000-680834\\/\\\">The Complete Singapore Sal<\\/a> (SS stories from #109, 111)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1935-the-golden-age-captain-ma\\/4000-682215\\/\\\">The Golden Age Captain Marvel: Volume 2<\\/a> (#21-25)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2075-the-golden-age-captain-ma\\/4000-680603\\/\\\">The Golden Age Captain Marvel: Volume 3<\\/a> (#26)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2051-golden-age-captain-marvel\\/4000-680761\\/\\\">Golden Age Captain Marvel Jr. Giant #1<\\/a> (CMJr's origin from #25)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1282-the-golden-age-spy-smashe\\/4000-681627\\/\\\">The Golden Age Spy Smasher: Volume 4<\\/a> (SS stories from #43-50)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-188-golden-arrow-volume-1\\/4000-683389\\/\\\">Golden Arrow: Volume 1<\\/a> (GA stories from #2, 7-43)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\