nture comics, the primary feature being Rangers of Freedom from which the series took its name. The comic published at a bimonthly rate and after a year (seven issues) the series name shortened and it became <a data-ref-id=\\\"4050-19318\\\" href=\\\"\\/rangers-comics\\/4050-19318\\/\\\" slug=\\\"rangers-comics\\\">Rangers Comics<\\/a> with #8, a title which it kept for many more years until it was cancelled over a decade later.<\\/p>\",\"first_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-256516\\/\",\"id\":256516,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"1\"},\"id\":879,\"image\":{\"icon_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_avatar\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"medium_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_medium\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"screen_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_medium\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"screen_large_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_kubrick\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"small_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_small\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"super_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_large\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"thumb_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_avatar\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"tiny_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_mini\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"original_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/original\\/1618451-1.jpg\",\"image_tags\":\"All Images\"},\"last_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-256528\\/\",\"id\":256528,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"7\"},\"name\":\"Rangers of Freedom Comics\",\"publisher\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/publisher\\/4010-8\\/\",\"id\":8,\"name\":\"Fiction House\"},\"site_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/rangers-of-freedom-comics\\/4050-879\\/\",\"start_year\":\"1941\"},{\"aliases\":null,\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/volume\\/4050-886\\/\",\"count_of_issues\":134,\"date_added\":\"2008-06-06 11:08:04\",\"date_last_updated\":\"2018-09-18 14:30:04\",\"deck\":null,\"description\":\"<p>Daredevil Comics, one of Lev Gleason Publication's longest-running comics was a Golden Age anthology comic that took its name from its main feature character <a href=\\\"\\/death-defying-devil\\/4005-25994\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-25994\\\">Daredevil<\\/a> (named \\\"The Death-Defying Devil\\\" in Dynamite Entertainment comics and \\\"Red Devil\\\" at AC Comics as not to be confused with the Marvel character but called by his original name, Daredevil, at Image Comics). Daredevil was eventually phased out of the title in the late forties and for most of the comic's run, apart from the title the character wasn't the main feature anymore and the covers were primarily dominated by The Little Wise Guys.<\\/p><p><b>General Notes<\\/b><\\/p><p>The first issue was actually titled \\\"Daredevil Battles Hitler #1\\\".<\\/p><h4>Collected Editions<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1377-daredevil-and-the-claw-vo\\/4000-681692\\/\\\">Daredevil and The Claw: Volume 1<\\/a> (#1-3)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1421-daredevil-and-the-claw-vo\\/4000-681736\\/\\\">Daredevil and The Claw: Volume 3<\\/a> (#15-24)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1414-the-ghost-vs-the-claw-the\\/4000-681731\\/\\\">The Ghost Vs. The Claw: The Complete Series<\\/a> (G stories from #5-20)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.comicvine.com\\/the-original-daredevil-archives-1-volume-one\\/4000-413641\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4000-413641\\\">The Original Daredevil Archives vol. 1<\\/a> (#1-4)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"first_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-251917\\/\",\"id\":251917,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"24\"},\"id\":886,\"image\":{\"icon_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_avatar\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"medium_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_medium\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"screen_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_medium\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"screen_large_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_kubrick\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"small_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_small\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"super_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_large\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"thumb_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_avatar\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"tiny_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_mini\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"original_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/original\\/316019-886-123809-1-daredevil-comics.jpg\",\"image_tags\":\"All Images\"},\"last_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-2696\\/\",\"id\":2696,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"134\"},\"name\":\"Daredevil Comics\",\"publisher\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/publisher\\/4010-52\\/\",\"id\":52,\"name\":\"Lev Gleason\"},\"site_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/daredevil-comics\\/4050-886\\/\",\"start_year\":\"1941\"},{\"aliases\":null,\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/volume\\/4050-893\\/\",\"count_of_issues\":32,\"date_added\":\"2008-06-06 11:08:04\",\"date_last_updated\":\"2018-09-03 20:23:46\",\"deck\":null,\"description\":\"<p>Four Favorites was an inconsistently published anthology comic series that primarily focused on four specific characters per issue (the \\\"four favorites\\\"). The original line-up was all superheroes with \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/magno\\/4005-4110\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-4110\\\">Magno<\\/a> (and <a href=\\\"\\/davey\\/4005-61258\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-61258\\\">Davey<\\/a>)\\\", \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/lash-lightning\\/4005-34148\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-34148\\\">Lash Lightning<\\/a>\\\", \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/vulcan\\/4005-18744\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-18744\\\">Vulcan<\\/a>\\\" and \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/raven\\/4005-6537\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-6537\\\">The Raven<\\/a>\\\". With the fourth issue, Vulcan was switched out for <a href=\\\"\\/soldier-unknown\\/4005-61008\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-61008\\\">Unknown Soldier<\\/a> (predates the DC character of the same name) and in the following issue The Raven was replaced by <a href=\\\"\\/captain-courageous\\/4005-18821\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-18821\\\">Captain Courageous<\\/a>. The Flag took Captain Courageous' spot in the next issue, but with #7 Capt. Courageous returned and the line-up remained consistent up until the 21st issue when Unknown Soldier was replaced by an unrelated character called \\\"<a href=\\\"\\/the-unknown\\/4005-76050\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-76050\\\">The Unknown<\\/a>\\\". In #24, Lightning was replaced with <a href=\\\"\\/hap-hazard\\/4005-75788\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4005-75788\\\">Hap Hazard<\\/a> by which point the comic no longer retained a consistent genre and expanded into several. With #26, the last of the original features was cut and the line-up from that point on changed every issue until it settled on four characters for the last three issues but superheroes were no longer featured in the publication and when the series ended in 1947, it was a teen humor publication. Two issues followed #32, under different titles: #33 was called <a href=\\\"\\/crime-must-pay-the-penalty\\/4050-40505\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-40505\\\">Crime Must Pay the Penalty<\\/a> (which became its own long-running series) and #34 was titled <a href=\\\"\\/four-teeners\\/4050-32020\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4050-32020\\\">Four Teeners<\\/a>.<\\/p><h4>Collected Editions<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1184-the-complete-four-favorit\\/4000-681578\\/\\\">The Complete Four Favorites: Volume 1<\\/a> (#1-4)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1392-the-complete-four-favorit\\/4000-681703\\/\\\">The Complete Four Favorites: Volume 2<\\/a> (#5-8)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2104-the-complete-four-favorit\\/4000-681442\\/\\\">The Complete Four Favorites: Volume 5<\\/a> (#18-24)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2114-the-complete-unknown\\/4000-683588\\/\\\">The Complete Unknown<\\/a> (Uknown stories)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"first_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-158519\\/\",\"id\":158519,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"1\"},\"id\":893,\"image\":{\"icon_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_avatar\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"medium_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_medium\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"screen_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_medium\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"screen_large_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/screen_kubrick\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"small_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_small\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"super_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_large\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"thumb_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/scale_avatar\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"tiny_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/square_mini\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"original_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/image\\/original\\/816386-1.jpg\",\"image_tags\":\"All Images\"},\"last_issue\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/issue\\/4000-158534\\/\",\"id\":158534,\"name\":null,\"issue_number\":\"32\"},\"name\":\"Four Favorites\",\"publisher\":{\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/publisher\\/4010-32\\/\",\"id\":32,\"name\":\"Ace Magazines\"},\"site_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/four-favorites\\/4050-893\\/\",\"start_year\":\"1941\"},{\"aliases\":null,\"api_detail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/api\\/volume\\/4050-898\\/\",\"count_of_issues\":150,\"date_added\":\"2008-06-06 11:08:04\",\"date_last_updated\":\"2018-09-07 11:43:15\",\"deck\":null,\"description\":\"<p>Captain Marvel Adventures was one of several ongoings during the Golden Age starring Fawcett's Captain Marvel, who was more popular than Superman in the late 40's and early 50's. The series told the adventures of young Billy Batson, who by speaking the magic word \\\"SHAZAM!\\\" would receive super powers. Trouble was, these powers were kind of similar to those attributed to the Man of Steel. Depite the fact that Captain Marvel's stories tended to have a lighter and more humourous element to them, DC was not impressed. After a protracted plagiarism lawsuit, which DC eventually won, Cap and the rest of the Marvel Family disappeared from the comic world for about 20 years. Funnily enough, they would re-appear at DC.<\\/p><h4>Collected Editons:<\\/h4><ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-93-captain-kid\\/4000-680346\\/\\\" data-ref-id=\\\"4000-680346\\\">Captain Kid<\\/a> (CK stories from #5-104)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-1935-the-golden-age-captain-ma\\/4000-682215\\/\\\">The Golden Age Captain Marvel: Volume 2<\\/a> (#1-2)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/comicvine.gamespot.com\\/gwandanaland-comics-2038-sivana-golden-age-captain\\/4000-680806\\/\\\">Sivana - Golden Ag